Note:
========================================
HIR NODE-KIND CLASSIFICATION
========================================
:End Note

@Reasoning
A value read from a metadata node-slot or a children-list slot is a real HIR
node when its kind word (offset 0) falls in one of the documented HIR kind
bands: expressions/identifiers/literals (10000-10999 core, 17200-17556
translation), statements (11000-11999 core, 17100-17117 translation),
declarations (12000-12999 core, 17000-17016 translation), the type-system
band (13000-13999), pattern band (14000-14999), ownership band
(15000-15999), and the translation type/op bands (17300-17556). The
classification lets the cloner deep-copy genuine subtrees while leaving raw
scalar payloads untouched, and it backstops the metadata key classification
for any node-slot key.
@End Reasoning
Process called "is_hir_node_kind" that takes kind as Integer returns Integer:
    If kind is greater than or equal to 10000:
        If kind is less than 16000:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    If kind is greater than or equal to 17000:
        If kind is less than 17600:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note:
========================================
CORE DEEP CLONE
========================================
:End Note

@Reasoning
clone_node produces a structurally independent deep copy of an HIR subtree.
The copy preserves the node kind, the scalar value/value_type payload, the
attached HIRTypeInfo, scope id, symbol id, source position, and AST back-link,
then recursively duplicates the children list and every metadata-held
subtree. No node object is shared between the original and the clone, so a
subsequent transformation pass may rewrite the clone freely without disturbing
the source definition.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1. Allocate a fresh 104-byte HIRNode of the same kind via create_hir_node.
2. Copy the scalar header slots verbatim (value, value_type, type_info,
   scope_id, symbol_id, line, column, ast_node).
3. If a children list is present, clone each element (HIR_MAP_LITERAL stores
   16-byte key/value entry blocks rather than bare nodes, so its entries are
   cloned via clone_map_entry) and append the clone, maintaining child_count.
4. If a metadata dictionary is present, enumerate its keys and rebuild an
   independent dictionary: scalar keys copy verbatim, node-list keys clone
   each element into a fresh list, node-slot keys clone the single subtree.
   Cloned children and node-slot values have their parent pointer set to the
   clone so the duplicated tree is internally consistent.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
The dominant cost is the recursive descent and the per-node allocation; the
header copy is a fixed set of nine loads/stores. Metadata-key classification
is a short string-compare chain bounded by the small fixed key universe.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns a raw owned pointer into the HIR arena. The caller owns the clone and
must attach it to a parent (directly or through the splice operations) so the
tree walker reaches it during cleanup. Returns 0 on null input or allocation
failure; callers must check before dereferencing.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "clone_node" that takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let kind be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, NODE_TYPE_OFFSET)
    Let line be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, NODE_LINE_OFFSET)
    Let column be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, NODE_COLUMN_OFFSET)

    Let clone be HIR.create_hir_node(kind, line, column)
    If clone is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Copy scalar header slots verbatim (payload + bindings)
    Let value be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, NODE_VALUE_OFFSET)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(clone, NODE_VALUE_OFFSET, value)

    Let value_type be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, NODE_VALUE_TYPE_OFFSET)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(clone, NODE_VALUE_TYPE_OFFSET, value_type)

    Let type_info be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, NODE_TYPE_INFO_OFFSET)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(clone, NODE_TYPE_INFO_OFFSET, type_info)

    Let scope_id be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, NODE_SCOPE_ID_OFFSET)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(clone, NODE_SCOPE_ID_OFFSET, scope_id)

    Let symbol_id be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, NODE_SYMBOL_ID_OFFSET)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(clone, NODE_SYMBOL_ID_OFFSET, symbol_id)

    Let ast_node be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, NODE_AST_NODE_OFFSET)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(clone, NODE_AST_NODE_OFFSET, ast_node)

    Note: Clone the children list (if any)
    Let children be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, NODE_CHILDREN_OFFSET)
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let cloned_children be List.list_create()
        Let child_total be List.list_length(children)
        Let child_idx be 0
        While child_idx is less than child_total:
            Let child be List.list_get(children, child_idx)
            Let cloned_child be 0
            If kind is equal to HIRNodes.HIR_MAP_LITERAL:
                Set cloned_child to clone_map_entry(child)
            Otherwise:
                Set cloned_child to clone_node(child)
                If cloned_child is not equal to 0:
                    Layout.memory_set_int64(cloned_child, NODE_PARENT_OFFSET, clone)
                End If
            End If
            List.append(cloned_children, cloned_child)
            Set child_idx to (child_idx plus 1)
        End While
        Layout.memory_set_int64(clone, NODE_CHILDREN_OFFSET, cloned_children)
        Layout.memory_set_int64(clone, NODE_CHILD_COUNT_OFFSET, child_total)
    End If

    Note: Clone the metadata dictionary (if any)
    Let meta be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, NODE_METADATA_OFFSET)
    If meta is not equal to 0:
        Let cloned_meta be Dict.create()
        Let keys be Dict.keys(meta)
        Let key_total be List.list_length(keys)
        Let key_idx be 0
        While key_idx is less than key_total:
            Let key be List.list_get(keys, key_idx)
            Let entry_value be Dict.get(meta, key)

            If is_scalar_metadata_key(key) is equal to 1:
                Dict.set(cloned_meta, key, entry_value)
            Otherwise:
                If is_node_list_metadata_key(key) is equal to 1:
                    Let cloned_list be clone_node_list(entry_value, clone)
                    Dict.set(cloned_meta, key, cloned_list)
                Otherwise:
                    Note: Default: single node slot, or an unclassified scalar.
                    Note: Probe the kind word; clone only genuine HIR nodes.
                    If entry_value is equal to 0:
                        Dict.set(cloned_meta, key, 0)
                    Otherwise:
                        Let slot_kind be Layout.memory_get_int64(entry_value, NODE_TYPE_OFFSET)
                        If is_hir_node_kind(slot_kind) is equal to 1:
                            Let cloned_slot be clone_node(entry_value)
                            If cloned_slot is not equal to 0:
                                Layout.memory_set_int64(cloned_slot, NODE_PARENT_OFFSET, clone)
                            End If
                            Dict.set(cloned_meta, key, cloned_slot)
                        Otherwise:
                            Dict.set(cloned_meta, key, entry_value)
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If

            Set key_idx to (key_idx plus 1)
        End While
        Layout.memory_set_int64(clone, NODE_METADATA_OFFSET, cloned_meta)
    End If

    Return clone
End Process

@Reasoning
Node-list metadata values (argument lists, member lists, etc.) are ordered
Lists of HIR nodes. Cloning produces a fresh List whose elements are deep
clones re-parented under the owning clone, preserving order and ownership.
@End Reasoning
Process called "clone_node_list" that takes source_list as Integer, new_parent as Integer returns Integer:
    If source_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let cloned_list be List.list_create()
    Let total be List.list_length(source_list)
    Let idx be 0
    While idx is less than total:
        Let element be List.list_get(source_list, idx)
        Let cloned_element be clone_node(element)
        If cloned_element is not equal to 0:
            Layout.memory_set_int64(cloned_element, NODE_PARENT_OFFSET, new_parent)
        End If
        List.append(cloned_list, cloned_element)
        Set idx to (idx plus 1)
    End While

    Return cloned_list
End Process

@Reasoning
A HIR_MAP_LITERAL stores each entry as a 16-byte block laid out
[key_expr(0), value_expr(8)] (per hir_add_map_entry). Cloning an entry
duplicates both expression nodes into a fresh block so the cloned map owns
independent key/value subtrees.
@End Reasoning
Process called "clone_map_entry" that takes entry as Integer returns Integer:
    If entry is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let cloned_entry be Layout.allocate(16)
    If cloned_entry is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let key_expr be Layout.memory_get_int64(entry, 0)
    Let value_expr be Layout.memory_get_int64(entry, 8)

    Let cloned_key be clone_node(key_expr)
    Let cloned_value be clone_node(value_expr)

    Layout.memory_set_int64(cloned_entry, 0, cloned_key)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(cloned_entry, 8, cloned_value)

    Return cloned_entry
End Process

Note:
========================================
VARIABLE SUBSTITUTION
========================================
:End Note

@Reasoning
substitute_variables rewrites identifier references inside a cloned subtree
according to a name -> replacement-node mapping. Inlining builds this mapping
from each callee parameter name to the corresponding caller argument; after
substitution the cloned body reads its inputs directly from the call's
argument expressions rather than from parameters that no longer exist.

The mapping is keyed by parameter name (string) because HIR_IDENTIFIER nodes
carry their name in the value slot and that name is the stable join key
between a parameter declaration (HIR_PARAMETER "name" property) and its uses.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk the subtree. At each HIR_IDENTIFIER node, look up its name in the mapping;
if present, splice the mapped replacement in place of the identifier within its
owning parent slot (children list entry or metadata node slot). The walk
descends through the children list and every metadata node/node-list slot,
mirroring clone_node's structure so no reachable identifier is missed. The
substitution operates on the cloned tree in place and returns the (possibly
unchanged) root.
@End Implementation

@Security_Scope
Mutates the supplied subtree in place; callers pass a freshly cloned body, not
a shared original. The mapping dictionary is read-only here. Replacement nodes
are taken verbatim (their parent pointer is updated to the new owner), so they
must not be shared across multiple substitution sites unless the caller
intends aliasing; inlining clones arguments per call site to avoid this.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "substitute_variables" that takes node as Integer, mapping as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return node
    End If
    If mapping is equal to 0:
        Return node
    End If

    Note: Descend into the children list, substituting in place.
    Let children be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, NODE_CHILDREN_OFFSET)
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let kind be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, NODE_TYPE_OFFSET)
        Let child_total be List.list_length(children)
        Let child_idx be 0
        While child_idx is less than child_total:
            Let child be List.list_get(children, child_idx)
            If kind is equal to HIRNodes.HIR_MAP_LITERAL:
                substitute_map_entry(child, mapping)
            Otherwise:
                Let replacement be try_substitute_identifier(child, mapping)
                If replacement is not equal to child:
                    Layout.memory_set_int64(replacement, NODE_PARENT_OFFSET, node)
                    List.list_set(children, child_idx, replacement)
                Otherwise:
                    substitute_variables(child, mapping)
                End If
            End If
            Set child_idx to (child_idx plus 1)
        End While
    End If

    Note: Descend into metadata node and node-list slots.
    Let meta be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, NODE_METADATA_OFFSET)
    If meta is not equal to 0:
        Let keys be Dict.keys(meta)
        Let key_total be List.list_length(keys)
        Let key_idx be 0
        While key_idx is less than key_total:
            Let key be List.list_get(keys, key_idx)

            If is_scalar_metadata_key(key) is equal to 1:
                Note: Scalar payloads are never variable references.
                Set key_idx to (key_idx plus 1)
            Otherwise:
                If is_node_list_metadata_key(key) is equal to 1:
                    Let slot_list be Dict.get(meta, key)
                    substitute_node_list(slot_list, node, mapping)
                    Set key_idx to (key_idx plus 1)
                Otherwise:
                    Let slot be Dict.get(meta, key)
                    If slot is equal to 0:
                        Set key_idx to (key_idx plus 1)
                    Otherwise:
                        Let slot_kind be Layout.memory_get_int64(slot, NODE_TYPE_OFFSET)
                        If is_hir_node_kind(slot_kind) is equal to 1:
                            Let slot_replacement be try_substitute_identifier(slot, mapping)
                            If slot_replacement is not equal to slot:
                                Layout.memory_set_int64(slot_replacement, NODE_PARENT_OFFSET, node)
                                Dict.set(meta, key, slot_replacement)
                            Otherwise:
                                substitute_variables(slot, mapping)
                            End If
                        End If
                        Set key_idx to (key_idx plus 1)
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End While
    End If

    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning
For a node-list slot, each element may itself be a variable reference (e.g. an
identifier passed positionally) or a deeper subtree. We substitute each
element in place, re-parenting any direct replacement.
@End Reasoning
Process called "substitute_node_list" that takes slot_list as Integer, owner as Integer, mapping as Integer returns Integer:
    If slot_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let total be List.list_length(slot_list)
    Let idx be 0
    While idx is less than total:
        Let element be List.list_get(slot_list, idx)
        Let replacement be try_substitute_identifier(element, mapping)
        If replacement is not equal to element:
            Layout.memory_set_int64(replacement, NODE_PARENT_OFFSET, owner)
            List.list_set(slot_list, idx, replacement)
        Otherwise:
            substitute_variables(element, mapping)
        End If
        Set idx to (idx plus 1)
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
A HIR_MAP_LITERAL entry holds two expression slots; each may be or contain a
variable reference, so both are substituted in place.
@End Reasoning
Process called "substitute_map_entry" that takes entry as Integer, mapping as Integer returns Integer:
    If entry is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let key_expr be Layout.memory_get_int64(entry, 0)
    Let key_replacement be try_substitute_identifier(key_expr, mapping)
    If key_replacement is not equal to key_expr:
        Layout.memory_set_int64(entry, 0, key_replacement)
    Otherwise:
        substitute_variables(key_expr, mapping)
    End If

    Let value_expr be Layout.memory_get_int64(entry, 8)
    Let value_replacement be try_substitute_identifier(value_expr, mapping)
    If value_replacement is not equal to value_expr:
        Layout.memory_set_int64(entry, 8, value_replacement)
    Otherwise:
        substitute_variables(value_expr, mapping)
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
If a node is an identifier whose name appears in the mapping, the mapped
replacement node is returned; otherwise the node is returned unchanged. The
caller distinguishes "substituted" from "unchanged" by pointer identity.
@End Reasoning
Process called "try_substitute_identifier" that takes node as Integer, mapping as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return node
    End If

    Let kind be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, NODE_TYPE_OFFSET)
    If kind is not equal to HIRNodes.HIR_IDENTIFIER:
        Return node
    End If

    Let name be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, NODE_VALUE_OFFSET)
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return node
    End If

    Let replacement be Dict.get(mapping, name)
    If replacement is equal to 0:
        Return node
    End If

    Return replacement
End Process

Note:
========================================
CALL-SITE DISCOVERY
========================================
:End Note

@Reasoning
find_call_sites locates every HIR_CALL_EXPR in a subtree whose callee resolves
to a target process definition, appending each matching call node to the
result list. Inlining iterates this list to substitute each call with the
callee body. A call matches when its callee identifier's resolved symbol id
equals the target's symbol id, or, when symbols are unresolved, when the
callee identifier name equals the target's process name.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Recursively walk the subtree (children list and metadata node / node-list
slots). At each HIR_CALL_EXPR, read its "callee" property; if the callee is an
identifier, compare its symbol id against the target's symbol id (HIRNode
offset 88 on the target's base node) and, as a fallback, its name against the
target's process name. Matching calls are appended to result_list. Returns the
number of call sites found.
@End Implementation
Process called "find_call_sites" that takes root as Integer, target_fn as Integer, result_list as Integer returns Integer:
    If root is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If result_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let target_symbol be 0
    Let target_name be 0
    If target_fn is not equal to 0:
        Set target_symbol to Layout.memory_get_int64(target_fn, NODE_SYMBOL_ID_OFFSET)
        Set target_name to HIRNodes.hir_get_function_name(target_fn)
    End If

    Let found be 0
    Set found to find_call_sites_walk(root, target_symbol, target_name, result_list)
    Return found
End Process

@Reasoning
The recursive worker carries the resolved target identity (symbol id and name)
so each node is tested without re-deriving them. Both the children list and
metadata-held subtrees are visited so calls nested anywhere in the body are
discovered.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_call_sites_walk" that takes node as Integer, target_symbol as Integer, target_name as Integer, result_list as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let found be 0
    Let kind be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, NODE_TYPE_OFFSET)

    If kind is equal to HIRNodes.HIR_CALL_EXPR:
        If call_targets(node, target_symbol, target_name) is equal to 1:
            List.append(result_list, node)
            Set found to (found plus 1)
        End If
    End If

    Note: Visit children list.
    Let children be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, NODE_CHILDREN_OFFSET)
    If children is not equal to 0:
        If kind is equal to HIRNodes.HIR_MAP_LITERAL:
            Let entry_total be List.list_length(children)
            Let entry_idx be 0
            While entry_idx is less than entry_total:
                Let entry be List.list_get(children, entry_idx)
                If entry is not equal to 0:
                    Let key_expr be Layout.memory_get_int64(entry, 0)
                    Set found to (found plus find_call_sites_walk(key_expr, target_symbol, target_name, result_list))
                    Let value_expr be Layout.memory_get_int64(entry, 8)
                    Set found to (found plus find_call_sites_walk(value_expr, target_symbol, target_name, result_list))
                End If
                Set entry_idx to (entry_idx plus 1)
            End While
        Otherwise:
            Let child_total be List.list_length(children)
            Let child_idx be 0
            While child_idx is less than child_total:
                Let child be List.list_get(children, child_idx)
                Set found to (found plus find_call_sites_walk(child, target_symbol, target_name, result_list))
                Set child_idx to (child_idx plus 1)
            End While
        End If
    End If

    Note: Visit metadata node and node-list slots.
    Let meta be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, NODE_METADATA_OFFSET)
    If meta is not equal to 0:
        Let keys be Dict.keys(meta)
        Let key_total be List.list_length(keys)
        Let key_idx be 0
        While key_idx is less than key_total:
            Let key be List.list_get(keys, key_idx)

            If is_scalar_metadata_key(key) is equal to 1:
                Set key_idx to (key_idx plus 1)
            Otherwise:
                If is_node_list_metadata_key(key) is equal to 1:
                    Let slot_list be Dict.get(meta, key)
                    If slot_list is not equal to 0:
                        Let elem_total be List.list_length(slot_list)
                        Let elem_idx be 0
                        While elem_idx is less than elem_total:
                            Let element be List.list_get(slot_list, elem_idx)
                            Set found to (found plus find_call_sites_walk(element, target_symbol, target_name, result_list))
                            Set elem_idx to (elem_idx plus 1)
                        End While
                    End If
                    Set key_idx to (key_idx plus 1)
                Otherwise:
                    Let slot be Dict.get(meta, key)
                    If slot is not equal to 0:
                        Let slot_kind be Layout.memory_get_int64(slot, NODE_TYPE_OFFSET)
                        If is_hir_node_kind(slot_kind) is equal to 1:
                            Set found to (found plus find_call_sites_walk(slot, target_symbol, target_name, result_list))
                        End If
                    End If
                    Set key_idx to (key_idx plus 1)
                End If
            End If
        End While
    End If

    Return found
End Process

@Reasoning
A call targets the function when its callee identifier resolves to the same
symbol, or (symbols unresolved) bears the same name. The callee is read via
the canonical "callee" accessor.
@End Reasoning
Process called "call_targets" that takes call_node as Integer, target_symbol as Integer, target_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Let callee be HIRNodes.hir_get_call_callee(call_node)
    If callee is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let callee_kind be Layout.memory_get_int64(callee, NODE_TYPE_OFFSET)
    If callee_kind is not equal to HIRNodes.HIR_IDENTIFIER:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Prefer resolved-symbol identity when both sides are resolved.
    If target_symbol is not equal to 0:
        Let callee_symbol be Layout.memory_get_int64(callee, NODE_SYMBOL_ID_OFFSET)
        If callee_symbol is not equal to 0:
            If callee_symbol is equal to target_symbol:
                Return 1
            End If
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    Note: Fallback: compare identifier name against the target name.
    If target_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let callee_name be Layout.memory_get_int64(callee, NODE_VALUE_OFFSET)
    If StringCore.string_equals(callee_name, target_name) is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note:
========================================
RETURN REWRITING
========================================
:End Note

@Reasoning
convert_returns_to_assignments rewrites every HIR_RETURN inside an inlined
body. A "Return e" becomes "Set result_var to e" followed by a jump to the
body's end label; a bare "Return" becomes just the jump. After this rewrite the
cloned body has no return statements and its value flows into result_var, which
the caller reads in place of the original call expression.

The transformation is performed in place on the cloned body. Each return is
replaced within its owning parent slot (children-list entry or metadata node
slot) by an assignment statement, and a jump-to-end-label statement is spliced
immediately after it so control leaves the inlined region exactly where the
call used to return.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk the cloned body. For each HIR_RETURN found in a block's children list:
1. Read the return value expression ("value" property).
2. Build an assignment: HIR_ASSIGN_EXPR with lhs = identifier(result_var
   name), operator = HIR_ASSIGN_SIMPLE, rhs = the return value (when present),
   wrapped in a HIR_EXPR_STMT.
3. Build a jump: a HIR_BREAK statement carrying the end label name in its
   "name" property (the inliner emits a labeled block whose end the break
   targets).
4. Replace the return entry with the assignment statement and insert the jump
   immediately after it, keeping child_count consistent.
For returns reached through a metadata node slot (e.g. an if-branch that is a
single return rather than a block), the slot is rewritten to a freshly built
two-statement block holding the assignment and the jump.
A return with no value yields just the jump (no assignment), since there is no
value to bind.
@End Implementation
Process called "convert_returns_to_assignments" that takes body as Integer, result_var as Integer, end_label as Integer returns Integer:
    If body is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let kind be Layout.memory_get_int64(body, NODE_TYPE_OFFSET)

    Note: Rewrite returns that live directly in a block's children list.
    Let children be Layout.memory_get_int64(body, NODE_CHILDREN_OFFSET)
    If children is not equal to 0:
        If kind is not equal to HIRNodes.HIR_MAP_LITERAL:
            Let idx be 0
            While idx is less than List.list_length(children):
                Let stmt be List.list_get(children, idx)
                Let stmt_kind be 0
                If stmt is not equal to 0:
                    Set stmt_kind to Layout.memory_get_int64(stmt, NODE_TYPE_OFFSET)
                End If

                If stmt_kind is equal to HIRNodes.HIR_RETURN:
                    Let assign_stmt be build_return_assignment(stmt, result_var)
                    Let jump_stmt be build_jump(end_label)

                    If assign_stmt is equal to 0:
                        Note: Void return: replace the return with just the jump.
                        Layout.memory_set_int64(jump_stmt, NODE_PARENT_OFFSET, body)
                        List.list_set(children, idx, jump_stmt)
                        Set idx to (idx plus 1)
                    Otherwise:
                        Layout.memory_set_int64(assign_stmt, NODE_PARENT_OFFSET, body)
                        List.list_set(children, idx, assign_stmt)
                        Layout.memory_set_int64(jump_stmt, NODE_PARENT_OFFSET, body)
                        List.insert(children, (idx plus 1), jump_stmt)
                        Let new_count be Layout.memory_get_int64(body, NODE_CHILD_COUNT_OFFSET)
                        Layout.memory_set_int64(body, NODE_CHILD_COUNT_OFFSET, (new_count plus 1))
                        Set idx to (idx plus 2)
                    End If
                Otherwise:
                    Note: Recurse into nested statement structure.
                    convert_returns_to_assignments(stmt, result_var, end_label)
                    Set idx to (idx plus 1)
                End If
            End While
        End If
    End If

    Note: Rewrite returns reached through metadata node slots (e.g. if-branch
    Note: that is a single return statement, or a loop body).
    Let meta be Layout.memory_get_int64(body, NODE_METADATA_OFFSET)
    If meta is not equal to 0:
        Let keys be Dict.keys(meta)
        Let key_total be List.list_length(keys)
        Let key_idx be 0
        While key_idx is less than key_total:
            Let key be List.list_get(keys, key_idx)

            If is_scalar_metadata_key(key) is equal to 1:
                Set key_idx to (key_idx plus 1)
            Otherwise:
                If is_node_list_metadata_key(key) is equal to 1:
                    Set key_idx to (key_idx plus 1)
                Otherwise:
                    Let slot be Dict.get(meta, key)
                    If slot is equal to 0:
                        Set key_idx to (key_idx plus 1)
                    Otherwise:
                        Let slot_kind be Layout.memory_get_int64(slot, NODE_TYPE_OFFSET)
                        If slot_kind is equal to HIRNodes.HIR_RETURN:
                            Let replacement_block be build_return_block(slot, result_var, end_label)
                            Layout.memory_set_int64(replacement_block, NODE_PARENT_OFFSET, body)
                            Dict.set(meta, key, replacement_block)
                        Otherwise:
                            If is_hir_node_kind(slot_kind) is equal to 1:
                                convert_returns_to_assignments(slot, result_var, end_label)
                            End If
                        End If
                        Set key_idx to (key_idx plus 1)
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End While
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Builds the assignment statement that captures a return value into the inline
result variable. Returns 0 when the return is void (no value) so the caller
emits only the jump.
@End Reasoning
Process called "build_return_assignment" that takes return_stmt as Integer, result_var as Integer returns Integer:
    Let value_expr be HIRNodes.hir_get_return_value(return_stmt)
    If value_expr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let lhs be HIRNodes.hir_create_identifier(result_var)
    Let assign be HIRNodes.hir_create_assign_expr(lhs, HIRNodes.HIR_ASSIGN_SIMPLE, value_expr)
    If assign is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let assign_stmt be HIRNodes.hir_create_expression_statement(assign)
    Return assign_stmt
End Process

@Reasoning
Builds the control-flow jump that leaves the inlined region. The break carries
the end-label name so the inliner's labeled wrapper block can resolve it.
@End Reasoning
Process called "build_jump" that takes end_label as Integer returns Integer:
    Let jump be HIRNodes.hir_create_break()
    If jump is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If end_label is not equal to 0:
        HIRNodes.hir_set_metadata(jump, "name", end_label)
    End If

    Return jump
End Process

@Reasoning
For a return reached as a single-statement branch, wraps the rewritten
assignment-and-jump in a fresh block so the branch slot remains a single
statement node.
@End Reasoning
Process called "build_return_block" that takes return_stmt as Integer, result_var as Integer, end_label as Integer returns Integer:
    Let block be HIRNodes.hir_create_block()
    If block is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let assign_stmt be build_return_assignment(return_stmt, result_var)
    If assign_stmt is not equal to 0:
        HIRNodes.hir_add_statement(block, assign_stmt)
    End If

    Let jump_stmt be build_jump(end_label)
    HIRNodes.hir_add_statement(block, jump_stmt)

    Return block
End Process

Note:
========================================
TREE SPLICING
========================================
:End Note

@Reasoning
replace_node swaps old_node for new_node within parent. The old node may be
held in the parent's children list or in a metadata node slot; both are
checked so the operation works regardless of how the parent references the
child. The new node's parent pointer is updated to parent.
@End Reasoning
Process called "replace_node" that takes parent as Integer, old_node as Integer, new_node as Integer returns Integer:
    If parent is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Children-list slot.
    Let children be Layout.memory_get_int64(parent, NODE_CHILDREN_OFFSET)
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let idx be List.list_index_of(children, old_node)
        If idx is greater than or equal to 0:
            List.list_set(children, idx, new_node)
            If new_node is not equal to 0:
                Layout.memory_set_int64(new_node, NODE_PARENT_OFFSET, parent)
            End If
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Note: Metadata node slot.
    Let meta be Layout.memory_get_int64(parent, NODE_METADATA_OFFSET)
    If meta is not equal to 0:
        Let keys be Dict.keys(meta)
        Let key_total be List.list_length(keys)
        Let key_idx be 0
        While key_idx is less than key_total:
            Let key be List.list_get(keys, key_idx)
            If is_scalar_metadata_key(key) is equal to 1:
                Set key_idx to (key_idx plus 1)
            Otherwise:
                If is_node_list_metadata_key(key) is equal to 1:
                    Let slot_list be Dict.get(meta, key)
                    If slot_list is not equal to 0:
                        Let lidx be List.list_index_of(slot_list, old_node)
                        If lidx is greater than or equal to 0:
                            List.list_set(slot_list, lidx, new_node)
                            If new_node is not equal to 0:
                                Layout.memory_set_int64(new_node, NODE_PARENT_OFFSET, parent)
                            End If
                            Return 1
                        End If
                    End If
                    Set key_idx to (key_idx plus 1)
                Otherwise:
                    Let slot be Dict.get(meta, key)
                    If slot is equal to old_node:
                        Dict.set(meta, key, new_node)
                        If new_node is not equal to 0:
                            Layout.memory_set_int64(new_node, NODE_PARENT_OFFSET, parent)
                        End If
                        Return 1
                    End If
                    Set key_idx to (key_idx plus 1)
                End If
            End If
        End While
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
insert_before inserts new_node immediately before anchor in parent's children
list. Splicing into a positional sequence is only meaningful for the
children-list representation (blocks, modules, list literals); the operation
returns 0 if anchor is not a list child.
@End Reasoning
Process called "insert_before" that takes parent as Integer, anchor as Integer, new_node as Integer returns Integer:
    If parent is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let children be Layout.memory_get_int64(parent, NODE_CHILDREN_OFFSET)
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let idx be List.list_index_of(children, anchor)
    If idx is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    List.insert(children, idx, new_node)
    If new_node is not equal to 0:
        Layout.memory_set_int64(new_node, NODE_PARENT_OFFSET, parent)
    End If

    Let count be Layout.memory_get_int64(parent, NODE_CHILD_COUNT_OFFSET)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(parent, NODE_CHILD_COUNT_OFFSET, (count plus 1))

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
insert_after inserts new_node immediately after anchor in parent's children
list, mirroring insert_before.
@End Reasoning
Process called "insert_after" that takes parent as Integer, anchor as Integer, new_node as Integer returns Integer:
    If parent is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let children be Layout.memory_get_int64(parent, NODE_CHILDREN_OFFSET)
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let idx be List.list_index_of(children, anchor)
    If idx is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    List.insert(children, (idx plus 1), new_node)
    If new_node is not equal to 0:
        Layout.memory_set_int64(new_node, NODE_PARENT_OFFSET, parent)
    End If

    Let count be Layout.memory_get_int64(parent, NODE_CHILD_COUNT_OFFSET)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(parent, NODE_CHILD_COUNT_OFFSET, (count plus 1))

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
remove_node detaches node from parent. As with replace_node, the node may be a
children-list entry or a metadata node slot; both are checked. Removing from
the children list shrinks it and decrements child_count; clearing a metadata
node slot writes 0.
@End Reasoning
Process called "remove_node" that takes parent as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    If parent is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let children be Layout.memory_get_int64(parent, NODE_CHILDREN_OFFSET)
    If children is not equal to 0:
        Let idx be List.list_index_of(children, node)
        If idx is greater than or equal to 0:
            List.remove_at(children, idx)
            Let count be Layout.memory_get_int64(parent, NODE_CHILD_COUNT_OFFSET)
            If count is greater than 0:
                Layout.memory_set_int64(parent, NODE_CHILD_COUNT_OFFSET, (count minus 1))
            End If
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Let meta be Layout.memory_get_int64(parent, NODE_METADATA_OFFSET)
    If meta is not equal to 0:
        Let keys be Dict.keys(meta)
        Let key_total be List.list_length(keys)
        Let key_idx be 0
        While key_idx is less than key_total:
            Let key be List.list_get(keys, key_idx)
            If is_node_list_metadata_key(key) is equal to 1:
                Let slot_list be Dict.get(meta, key)
                If slot_list is not equal to 0:
                    Let lidx be List.list_index_of(slot_list, node)
                    If lidx is greater than or equal to 0:
                        List.remove_at(slot_list, lidx)
                        Return 1
                    End If
                End If
                Set key_idx to (key_idx plus 1)
            Otherwise:
                If is_scalar_metadata_key(key) is equal to 1:
                    Set key_idx to (key_idx plus 1)
                Otherwise:
                    Let slot be Dict.get(meta, key)
                    If slot is equal to node:
                        Dict.set(meta, key, 0)
                        Return 1
                    End If
                    Set key_idx to (key_idx plus 1)
                End If
            End If
        End While
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note:
========================================
NODE SIZE ESTIMATION AND CONSTRUCTION
========================================
:End Note

@Reasoning
estimate_node_size returns a structural weight for a subtree: 1 for the node
itself plus the recursive weight of every child and metadata-held subtree.
Inlining and unrolling use this to bound code growth (callers compare the
result against a budget before duplicating a body).
@End Reasoning
Process called "estimate_node_size" that takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let total be 1
    Let kind be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, NODE_TYPE_OFFSET)

    Let children be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, NODE_CHILDREN_OFFSET)
    If children is not equal to 0:
        If kind is equal to HIRNodes.HIR_MAP_LITERAL:
            Let entry_total be List.list_length(children)
            Let entry_idx be 0
            While entry_idx is less than entry_total:
                Let entry be List.list_get(children, entry_idx)
                If entry is not equal to 0:
                    Let key_expr be Layout.memory_get_int64(entry, 0)
                    Set total to (total plus estimate_node_size(key_expr))
                    Let value_expr be Layout.memory_get_int64(entry, 8)
                    Set total to (total plus estimate_node_size(value_expr))
                End If
                Set entry_idx to (entry_idx plus 1)
            End While
        Otherwise:
            Let child_total be List.list_length(children)
            Let child_idx be 0
            While child_idx is less than child_total:
                Let child be List.list_get(children, child_idx)
                Set total to (total plus estimate_node_size(child))
                Set child_idx to (child_idx plus 1)
            End While
        End If
    End If

    Let meta be Layout.memory_get_int64(node, NODE_METADATA_OFFSET)
    If meta is not equal to 0:
        Let keys be Dict.keys(meta)
        Let key_total be List.list_length(keys)
        Let key_idx be 0
        While key_idx is less than key_total:
            Let key be List.list_get(keys, key_idx)
            If is_scalar_metadata_key(key) is equal to 1:
                Set key_idx to (key_idx plus 1)
            Otherwise:
                If is_node_list_metadata_key(key) is equal to 1:
                    Let slot_list be Dict.get(meta, key)
                    If slot_list is not equal to 0:
                        Let elem_total be List.list_length(slot_list)
                        Let elem_idx be 0
                        While elem_idx is less than elem_total:
                            Let element be List.list_get(slot_list, elem_idx)
                            Set total to (total plus estimate_node_size(element))
                            Set elem_idx to (elem_idx plus 1)
                        End While
                    End If
                    Set key_idx to (key_idx plus 1)
                Otherwise:
                    Let slot be Dict.get(meta, key)
                    If slot is not equal to 0:
                        Let slot_kind be Layout.memory_get_int64(slot, NODE_TYPE_OFFSET)
                        If is_hir_node_kind(slot_kind) is equal to 1:
                            Set total to (total plus estimate_node_size(slot))
                        End If
                    End If
                    Set key_idx to (key_idx plus 1)
                End If
            End If
        End While
    End If

    Return total
End Process

@Reasoning
create_int_literal builds a HIR_INT_LITERAL node carrying value, delegating to
the real translation-HIR producer so the literal is bit-identical to those the
frontends emit.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_int_literal" that takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    Return HIRNodes.hir_create_int_literal(value)
End Process

@Reasoning
get_type_info returns the HIRTypeInfo attached to a node, the pointer
get_type_size and get_type_alignment consume. It delegates to the canonical
core accessor so all consumers read the same slot.
@End Reasoning
Process called "get_type_info" that takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Return HIR.get_hir_node_type_info(node)
End Process
